        q: `A 72-year-old man has been taking nonsteroidal antiinflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) for the past two years because of chronic degenerative arthritis of the hips and knees. Over the past 2 weeks, he has had epigastric pain with nausea and vomiting and an episode of hematemesis. On physical examination, there are no remarkable findings. A gastric biopsy specimen shows shallow ulcerations with neutrophils. Which of the following is the most likely mechanism of the gastric lesions?`,
