        q: `A 67-year-old woman has experienced severe nausea, vomiting, early satiety, and a 9-kg weight loss over the past 4 months. On physical examination, she has muscle wasting. Upper gastrointestinal endoscopy shows that the entire gastric mucosa is eroded and rugal folds are lost. An abdominal CT scan shows that the stomach is small and shrunken. A biopsy shows sheets of mucin-filled cells infiltrating the gastric wall. Which of the following molecular alterations is most likely to be found in this lesion?`,
