        q: `A 61-year-old man with increasing fatigue, early satiety, and nausea for 5 months vomited dark granular material yesterday. Endoscopy reveals a large ulcerated mass in the gastric fundus. Biopsies are taken and microscopically the mass is composed of spindle cells that are positive for KIT with immunohistochemical staining. Mitoses are frequent. Gastrectomy is performed, and a 10-cm circumscribed mass is seen to arise from the gastric wall. Which of the following therapies is most likely to be a useful adjunct in treatment of his disease?`,
        q2: ``,
        q3: [],
