        q: `An 11-month-old, previously healthy infant has not produced stool for 1 day. The mother notices that the infant’s abdomen is distended. On physical examination, the infant’s abdomen is very tender, and bowel sounds are nearly absent. An abdominal plain film radiograph shows no free air, but there are distended loops of small bowel with air-fluid levels. Which of the following is most likely to produce these findings?`,
