        optionFeedback: [`Duodenal obstruction due to atresia is rare. It would present at birth and would not cause distal intestinal obstruction.`,`Hirschsprung disease presents with intestinal obstruction at birth.`,`<!--Answers:-->Failure to produce stool, abdominal distention, and absent bowel sounds are diagnostic of intestinal obstruction. The radiological findings confirm the diagnosis. Of the numerous causes of intestinal obstruction, the most common in previously healthy children under the age of 2 is intussusception. Its cause is usually unknown. `,`Meckel diverticulum is a usually asymptomatic outpouching of the wall of the ileum. When ectopic gastric mucosa is present, patients may present with symptoms of peptic ulcer disease.`,`Pyloric stenosis may be a consequence of chronic inflammation or a rare congenital lesion. It would cause gastric obstruction, not distal intestinal obstruction. `],
