        q: `A 31-year-old woman had increasingly severe diarrhea 1 week after returning from a trip to Central America. Gross examination of the stools showed mucus and streaks of blood. The diarrheal illness subsided within 4 weeks, but now she has become febrile and has pain in the right upper quadrant of the abdomen. An abdominal ultrasound scan shows a 10-cm, irregular, partly cystic mass in the right hepatic lobe. Which of the following infectious organisms is most likely to produce these findings?`,
