        q: `A 27-year-old man has a history of chronic intermittent abdominal pain, fever and diarrhea for the past 3 years which he had ascribed to indigestion. He has also noted 5Kg of weight loss in the past 6 months. He now presents with sudden onset of marked abdominal pain. On physical examination, his abdomen is diffusely tender and distended and bowel sounds are absent. He undergoes surgery and a segment of terminal ileum along with cecum with a firm, erythematous serosal surface, is removed. The gross appearance of the resected specimen is shown in the figure here. Which of the following complications occur most commonly in patients with this disease process?`,       
